<title>UK: EX-DIVIDENDS TO TAKE 7.96 POINTS OFF FTSE, AUG 18.</title>
<headline>EX-DIVIDENDS TO TAKE 7.96 POINTS OFF FTSE, AUG 18.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following FTSE 100 stocks will go ex-dividend on August 18 and analysts estimate the effect will be to take 7.96 points off the index on Monday.</p>
<p>						DIVIDEND   INDEX</p>
<p>						(PENCE)    EFFECT</p>
<p>COMPANY					  Net	 Net</p>
<p>* Barclays				    13.50    1.161</p>
<p>* Commercial Union Assurance Co   (a) 12.25    0.478</p>
<p>* GKN				     (a) 10.50    0.210</p>
<p>* HSBC Holdings (Ord 75p)		 20.00    1.000</p>
<p>* HSBC Holdings ($HK10)		   20.00    2.040</p>
<p>* Imperial Chemical Industries    (a) 12.50    0.513</p>
<p>* Reed International			12.50    0.813</p>
<p>* Royal &amp; Sun Alliance		     7.15    0.622</p>
<p>* Scottish Power			    12.33    0.826</p>
<p>* Standard Chartered			 5.25    0.294</p>
<p>(a) Dividend amounts for Commercial Union, GKN and ICI are Foreign Income Dividends (FIDs) only.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7954</p>
